HappyShop project - client/Picker - category

Purpose:
    Manages order picking operations, providing warehouse picker staff
    with interface to locate products, fulfill orders, and track picking
    progress following MVC pattern

PickerClient:
    Purpose:
    Main entry point and container for the picker application, managing the picker
    staff interface and application lifecycle on handheld devices or terminals.

    Responsibilities:
    - Launches the picker application on device
    - Initializes all picker MVC components
    - Manages the main picker window/screen
    - Handles navigation between picking screens
    - Manages picker session and authentication
    - Coordinates communication between picker modules
    - Handles application shutdown and cleanup
    - Manages device-specific features (scanner, screen size)
    - Initializes connection to warehouse system
    - Handles offline mode if network disconnected

    Usage:
    Created and launched when picker staff logs in on handheld device or terminal.
    Acts as main container for all picker functionality. Manages transitions
    between order list, picking screen, and completion screens. Maintains picker
    session throughout shift. Entry point for picker application on mobile devices.

PickerController:
    Purpose:
    Central controller that manages picking logic and coordinates interactions
    between PickerView, PickerModel, and warehouse system for order fulfillment.

    Responsibilities:
    - Handles user actions from PickerView
    - Assigns orders to pickers
    - Processes item scanning and picking confirmations
    - Validates picked quantities against order requirements
    - Manages picking workflow (item by item)
    - Coordinates with warehouse inventory system
    - Updates view based on model changes
    - Handles error scenarios (wrong item, insufficient stock)
    - Tracks picking progress and completion
    - Manages order completion and handoff
    - Validates barcode scans
    - Handles picking exceptions and corrections

    Usage:
    Created by PickerClient during initialization. Receives all user interactions
    from PickerView (scans, button clicks). Calls PickerModel for data operations
    and validation. Updates PickerView based on results. Coordinates entire picking
    workflow from order assignment to completion.

PickerModel:
    Purpose:
    Manages picker data, order information, and communicates with warehouse server
    to retrieve orders, validate picks, and update inventory after picking.

    Responsibilities:
    - Stores current picker information
    - Retrieves assigned orders from server
    - Maintains picking queue for current picker
    - Validates scanned items against order requirements
    - Updates order status as items are picked
    - Communicates with inventory system
    - Records picking transactions
    - Handles data persistence and synchronization
    - Manages offline data storage if network unavailable
    - Validates product barcodes
    - Tracks item locations in warehouse
    - Updates stock levels after picking

    Usage:
    Called by PickerController to perform data operations. Communicates with
    warehouse server and database. Maintains current picking state. Provides order
    and product data to controller. Validates all picking operations. Handles
    synchronization between handheld device and main system.

PickerUIStyles:
    Purpose:
    Defines visual styling, themes, colors, and layout constants for the picker
    interface optimized for handheld devices and quick scanning operations.

    Properties:
    - Color scheme: High contrast colors for warehouse environment
    - Success color: Green for correct picks
    - Error color: Red for wrong items or errors
    - Warning color: Yellow for attention needed
    - Font families: Large, bold fonts for readability
    - Font sizes: Extra large for viewing from distance/while moving
    - Button styles: Large touch-friendly buttons
    - Spacing constants: Generous spacing for ease of use
    - Border styles: Clear visual separation
    - Icon sizes: Large icons for quick recognition
    - Status indicators: Color-coded status badges
    - Scan feedback: Visual and audio cues for scans

    Responsibilities:
    - Provides consistent color palette for picker interface
    - Defines large, touch-friendly UI elements
    - Ensures high visibility in warehouse lighting
    - Makes UI optimized for mobile/handheld devices
    - Supports quick visual feedback (colors, animations)
    - Defines layout for small screens
    - Provides accessibility for various lighting conditions
    - Ensures color-blind friendly design

    Usage:
    Used by PickerView to style all UI components for handheld devices. Applied
    when creating buttons, labels, and status indicators. Ensures picker
    application is easy to use while walking and scanning. Optimized for quick
    glances and touch interaction. Makes interface visible in various warehouse
    lighting conditions.

PickerView:
    Purpose:
    Provides the graphical user interface for picker staff on handheld devices,
    displaying order details, item locations, and picking progress with large,
    touch-friendly controls.

    UI Components:
    - Current order summary panel
    - Item to pick display (large, prominent)
      * Product name
      * Product image
      * Quantity needed
      * Warehouse location (aisle, bin)
    - Barcode scanner input
    - Quantity confirmation buttons (large + and - buttons)
    - "Confirm Pick" button (large, green)
    - "Report Issue" button
    - Progress indicator (items picked / total items)
    - Current item location indicator
    - Pick list (remaining items)
    - Order details section
    - Success/error message display
    - Scanner status indicator

    Responsibilities:
    - Renders picker UI optimized for handheld devices
    - Displays current item to pick with prominent details
    - Shows warehouse location clearly (aisle, bin number)
    - Captures barcode scans via device scanner
    - Provides large touch-friendly buttons
    - Sends picking events to PickerController
    - Updates display based on controller commands
    - Applies PickerUIStyle to all components
    - Provides visual feedback for scans (green/red flash)
    - Shows picking progress
    - Displays error messages clearly
    - Provides audio feedback for successful scans
    - Shows next item automatically after confirmation

    Usage:
    Created by PickerClient during initialization. Controlled by PickerController.
    Displays picking interface on handheld device. Captures scans and button
    presses. Sends events to controller. Updated by controller as picking
    progresses. Optimized for one-handed use while holding scanner. Primary
    interface for picker staff during order fulfillment.